# C++ Interview Workspace Context

## Toolchain
- Compiler: GCC 11.4.0. **No** `std::expected` (needs GCC 12+). **No** `std::format` (needs GCC 13+)
- CMake 4.3.2 via pip3. Add to PATH: `export PATH="$(python3 -c 'import cmake; print(cmake.CMAKE_BIN_DIR)'):$PATH"`
- Generator: "Unix Makefiles" — Ninja is not installed
- All `CMakePresets.json` files use `"version": 3` (CMake 3.22+ compatible)

## CMake Patterns
- `require_cpp20(target)` in `cmake/modules/StandardVersion.cmake` — detects INTERFACE libraries and adjusts visibility automatically
- Always use `gtest_discover_tests(target DISCOVERY_MODE PRE_TEST)` — sanitized binaries cannot run at build time
- Shared CMake modules live in `cmake/modules/`; projects add them with:
  ```cmake
  list(APPEND CMAKE_MODULE_PATH "${CMAKE_SOURCE_DIR}/../../cmake/modules")
  ```

## Sanitizers on WSL2
- ASan/LeakSan: work. Run via `cmake --preset asan && ctest --preset asan`
- TSan: **cannot execute** in WSL2 — `FATAL: ThreadSanitizer: unexpected memory mapping`. Build-only verification is fine
- UBSan: works

## Project Structure
```
projects/<NN-name>/    ← each project: own CMakeLists.txt + CMakePresets.json
tutorial/              ← 24-chapter C++ bible (owned by Forge)
docs/superpowers/
  specs/               ← specifications
  plans/               ← implementation plans (naming: YYYY-MM-DD-<project>-NN-<phase>.md)
cmake/modules/         ← shared CMake modules
.agents/               ← multi-agent coordination
```

## foundation library (02-foundation) API
- `Buffer::data()` returns `std::byte*` — use `std::byte{val}` to assign, `std::to_integer<int>()` to read
- `Sorter<Policy>::sort(first, last)` takes iterators, not a container
- `TypeList<...>::size` is a static constexpr member — use `L::size`, not a separate trait

## Documentation
- All docs and diagrams as `.md` with Mermaid blocks — no browser tools
- Split large plans by pillar/phase when content exceeds ~1000 lines
